WEBVTT

00:02.306 --> 00:04.874
[Melody]
Our story is about a town...

00:04.917 --> 00:06.658
No, scratch that.

00:06.702 --> 00:09.444
Our story is about
three young women,

00:09.487 --> 00:11.446
bursting with talent.

00:11.489 --> 00:13.317
They were the best of friends

00:13.361 --> 00:15.841
until, sadly, they weren't.

00:15.885 --> 00:19.280
Our story is about
how they parted ways,

00:19.323 --> 00:22.326
found their own unique voices,

00:22.370 --> 00:24.502
and then rediscovered
each other,

00:24.546 --> 00:26.374
but not without some drama.

00:26.417 --> 00:31.509
Okay, I would like
to make a toast

00:31.553 --> 00:34.991
to my roommate
and my best friend,

00:35.035 --> 00:36.688
Melody Valentine,

00:36.732 --> 00:39.430
who, against all odds,
left law school

00:39.474 --> 00:42.651
in order to, uh,
write and publish

00:42.694 --> 00:45.262
her very first novel,
Summer Storm.

00:45.306 --> 00:47.264
I'm so proud of you.

00:47.308 --> 00:49.875
You fearlessly
chased your dream

00:49.919 --> 00:51.703
and you're a badass for it.

00:52.661 --> 00:53.705
I love you.

00:53.749 --> 00:55.229
[chuckles] Cheers.

00:55.272 --> 00:57.361
[all] Cheers.

01:00.234 --> 01:02.714
Thank you, Val, I love you.

01:02.758 --> 01:04.238
I love you so much.

01:05.674 --> 01:07.067
[sighs]

01:07.110 --> 01:10.766
As my best friend mentioned,
I was gonna be a lawyer.

01:10.809 --> 01:13.856
But when I started
looking for my voice,

01:13.899 --> 01:15.510
I knew I wasn't gonna find it

01:15.553 --> 01:17.903
inside of Harvard's
law library.

01:17.947 --> 01:19.340
[all chuckle softly]

01:19.383 --> 01:23.213
It was inside of me...
in the form of this book.

01:23.779 --> 01:25.215
I just...

01:25.259 --> 01:27.609
I guess I just had to be
brave enough to listen to it.

01:28.436 --> 01:29.437
And?

01:29.480 --> 01:32.092
It's not just gonna be a book.

01:32.135 --> 01:34.137
Tell everyone
the good news, babe.

01:34.181 --> 01:38.228
Okay! Well, it's not
"official" official,

01:38.272 --> 01:41.405
-but my book's been optioned.
-By Tyler Perry.

01:41.449 --> 01:43.320
And it's gonna be a movie,

01:43.364 --> 01:46.497
-and the best part is...
-[Melody chuckles]

01:47.455 --> 01:49.109
Well, I'm really excited,

01:49.152 --> 01:52.329
because it looks like Valerie's
gonna play the lead.

01:52.373 --> 01:56.333
[all cheering]

01:56.377 --> 01:58.205
Cheers to that.

01:58.248 --> 01:59.815
Cheers to that.

02:02.165 --> 02:04.385
That was such a fun party,
my love.

02:04.428 --> 02:06.604
I'm so glad we celebrated you.

02:07.214 --> 02:08.954
Me too, baby.

02:08.998 --> 02:12.132
Though, I do wish
you didn't bring up
the whole movie thing.

02:12.175 --> 02:13.350
Why is that?

02:14.960 --> 02:17.833
Tyler wants a big star,
to play the lead.

02:19.356 --> 02:20.705
Someone splashy,

02:20.749 --> 02:23.317
like Keke Palmer
or Amandla Stenberg.

02:23.839 --> 02:24.753
Not Val?

02:26.581 --> 02:27.886
No.

02:27.930 --> 02:30.585
Not if we want
the movie to get made, he says.

02:32.021 --> 02:32.891
[kisses hand]

02:35.677 --> 02:38.854
-That was a fun night.
-It was amazing!

02:38.897 --> 02:40.943
I'm so proud of Melody.

02:40.986 --> 02:42.771
She's like a real adult.

02:42.814 --> 02:44.990
You too, movie star.

02:45.034 --> 02:46.862
We're not there yet.

02:46.905 --> 02:48.298
I'm still a barista.

02:48.342 --> 02:49.560
Oh, please!

02:49.604 --> 02:51.301
You are so much more than that.

02:51.345 --> 02:55.175
You are a poet, an actress,
an activist,

02:55.218 --> 02:56.828
-the love of my life...
-Alan,

02:56.872 --> 02:59.701
-you're making me blush.
-[both chuckle]

03:00.876 --> 03:02.660
Speaking of,

03:02.704 --> 03:05.663
I know that you said
you needed some time
to think it over,

03:05.707 --> 03:07.143
but...

03:07.187 --> 03:10.320
I was wondering, if maybe,
you have an answer for me.

03:10.364 --> 03:13.105
Yeah, I have been thinking,
I promise,

03:13.149 --> 03:15.456
but I'm still unsure.

03:15.499 --> 03:18.110
Getting married is
such a big step.

03:18.154 --> 03:22.202
Okay, well, no pressure,
because I'm fine, either way.

03:23.246 --> 03:25.292
Just let me know,
when you decide.

03:25.335 --> 03:27.859
I will.

03:27.903 --> 03:33.038
And until then, just know that
I love you, Alan Mayberry,

03:33.082 --> 03:34.518
no matter what.

03:34.562 --> 03:35.737
I love you too, Val.

03:39.175 --> 03:40.220
[kissing]

03:40.263 --> 03:42.352
♪ ...kiss my hand ♪

03:42.396 --> 03:44.702
[man on radio] And that was
"Kiss My Hand,"

03:44.746 --> 03:47.270
the latest, number one single
from the multi-platinum
recording artist,

03:47.314 --> 03:49.446
Josie McCoy,

03:49.490 --> 03:51.448
even as the mystery surrounding
the superstar's whereabouts,
continues.

03:51.492 --> 03:54.582
After failing to appear
on stage this weekend,
in Berlin,

03:54.625 --> 03:56.105
-[bell dings]
-the world wants to know...

03:56.148 --> 03:59.413
what happened,
where did Josie vanish to?

03:59.456 --> 04:02.764
Excuse me, I'd like to place
an order to go.

04:02.807 --> 04:05.636
Double cheeseburger,
cheese fries and
a chocolate shake.

04:05.680 --> 04:07.247
[instrumental music playing]

04:07.290 --> 04:08.857
Wait, where's Pop Tate?

04:08.900 --> 04:12.426
Oh, that's my grandpa, he...
retired.

04:15.124 --> 04:16.343
[exclaiming in surprise]

04:16.386 --> 04:17.474
Oh, my God.
Are you...

04:18.301 --> 04:19.476
Are you Josie?

04:19.520 --> 04:23.088
Are you... "the" Josie McCoy?

04:23.132 --> 04:25.090
In the flesh, in the faux fur.

04:25.134 --> 04:26.353
[exclaiming in surprise]

04:26.396 --> 04:29.051
Unbelievable!
Josie McCoy, in my diner,

04:29.094 --> 04:30.792
I... this is... such an honor!

04:30.835 --> 04:33.882
At the risk of fangirling,
even more than I already am,

04:33.925 --> 04:36.363
I... I have to ask.

04:36.406 --> 04:39.061
What brought you to Riverdale?

04:39.104 --> 04:42.282
Just needed to take
a little break... for a while.

04:42.325 --> 04:44.501
You know, some me time,

04:44.545 --> 04:46.677
to re-center myself
and to write.

04:46.721 --> 04:48.200
Well, what's it like
being back?

04:48.244 --> 04:49.289
Is...

04:49.332 --> 04:50.986
Is it how you remember?

04:51.029 --> 04:52.683
[instrumental music playing]

04:58.385 --> 05:04.260
♪ There were nights
When the wind was so cold ♪

05:04.304 --> 05:06.523
♪ That my body froze in bed

05:06.567 --> 05:12.399
♪ If I just listened to it
Right outside the window ♪

05:14.357 --> 05:19.928
♪ There were days
When the sun was so cruel ♪

05:19.971 --> 05:22.322
♪ That all the tears
Turned to dust ♪

05:22.365 --> 05:27.805
♪ And I just knew my eyes
Were drying up forever ♪

05:30.895 --> 05:35.639
♪ I finished crying
In the instant that you left ♪

05:35.683 --> 05:40.905
♪ And I can't remember
Where or when or how ♪

05:40.949 --> 05:43.343
♪ And I banished every memory

05:43.386 --> 05:49.610
♪ You and I had ever made

05:49.653 --> 05:51.655
[footsteps approaching]

05:51.699 --> 05:54.049
♪ But when you touch me
Like this ♪

05:55.398 --> 05:58.183
♪ And you hold me like that

05:58.227 --> 05:59.924
♪ I just have to admit

05:59.968 --> 06:04.494
♪ That it's all coming
back to me ♪

06:04.538 --> 06:06.061
♪ It's all coming back

06:06.104 --> 06:10.195
♪ It's all coming
Back to me now ♪

06:10.239 --> 06:12.197
♪ There were moments of gold

06:12.241 --> 06:15.070
♪ And there flashes of light

06:15.113 --> 06:17.202
♪ There were things
I'd never do again ♪

06:17.246 --> 06:20.423
♪ But then
They'd always seemed right ♪

06:20.467 --> 06:22.817
♪ There were nights
Of endless pleasure ♪

06:22.860 --> 06:28.997
♪ It was more than
Any laws allowed ♪

06:29.693 --> 06:31.695
♪ Baby, baby

06:31.739 --> 06:34.568
♪ If I kiss you like this

06:34.611 --> 06:37.701
♪ And if you whisper
Like that ♪

06:37.745 --> 06:39.834
♪ It was lost long ago

06:39.877 --> 06:43.707
♪ But it's all coming
Back to me ♪

06:43.751 --> 06:48.408
♪ But you were history
With the slamming of the door ♪

06:48.451 --> 06:53.413
♪ And I made myself
So strong again somehow ♪

06:53.456 --> 07:00.115
♪ And I never wasted any
Of my time on you since then ♪

07:04.380 --> 07:06.121
♪ It's all coming back

07:06.164 --> 07:09.733
♪ It's all coming back
To me now ♪

07:09.777 --> 07:12.083
♪ When you see me like this

07:12.127 --> 07:15.260
♪ And when I see you
Like that ♪

07:15.304 --> 07:18.307
♪ Then we see
What we want to see ♪

07:18.350 --> 07:20.352
♪ All coming back to me

07:20.396 --> 07:22.311
♪ I can barely recall

07:22.354 --> 07:30.275
♪ But it's all coming back
To me now ♪

07:30.319 --> 07:31.538
[knock on door]

07:36.194 --> 07:38.849
I thought I told
the front desk, no autographs.

07:38.893 --> 07:41.112
I am so sorry, Ms. Newmar,

07:41.156 --> 07:45.769
but hotel policy, no live music
in our rooms after nine p.m.

07:45.813 --> 07:47.467
There have been complaints.

07:47.510 --> 07:49.512
Damn, Mr. Lodge.

07:49.556 --> 07:51.558
Nice to know
you're still a little bitch.

07:52.210 --> 07:54.169
Excuse me?

07:54.212 --> 07:56.476
What makes you think
you can speak to me that way?

07:56.519 --> 08:00.741
Uh, well, for starters,
you're here in your jammies,

08:00.784 --> 08:03.657
whining that my music's
too loud,

08:03.700 --> 08:07.965
To me, that screams,
"Once a little bitch,
always a little bitch."

08:09.358 --> 08:12.404
Move him, if he's got
a problem with my music.

08:12.448 --> 08:13.580
Excellent idea, Ms. Newmar.

08:13.623 --> 08:14.624
Just... just turn it down.

08:14.668 --> 08:15.843
[door slams]

08:26.331 --> 08:28.638
Veronica, do you have a minute?

08:29.857 --> 08:31.859
For you, Tabitha?
I've got five.

08:33.382 --> 08:35.166
So...

08:35.210 --> 08:39.649
I just had an encounter
with someone who really
inspires me.

08:39.693 --> 08:40.998
I won't say who, but...

08:42.130 --> 08:44.436
she reminded me of why I
came to Riverdale.

08:44.480 --> 08:48.658
My dream, my ambition,
which is to franchise Pop's.

08:48.702 --> 08:51.400
But to do that,
I need more capital, so...

08:51.443 --> 08:54.751
I thought, maybe, I could
give you my nest egg
to invest?

08:56.100 --> 08:58.712
Right now probably
isn't the best time.

08:58.755 --> 09:00.017
Why's that?

09:00.061 --> 09:03.194
Chad pulled me
into financial quicksand.

09:03.238 --> 09:06.502
A Ponzi scheme I'm trying
to dig myself out of,
by trading again.

09:06.546 --> 09:10.593
But it'll be months before
I can cover what Chad stole
from his clients

09:10.637 --> 09:12.203
in our name.

09:12.247 --> 09:16.251
And should any of our investors
start pulling out,

09:16.294 --> 09:18.993
the whole house of cards,
comes crashing down.

09:19.646 --> 09:21.299
Got it.

09:21.343 --> 09:22.257
Enough said.

09:23.127 --> 09:24.172
Good luck to you.

09:24.215 --> 09:25.739
Thanks.

09:25.782 --> 09:26.783
[knock on door]

09:26.827 --> 09:28.611
Waldo, look who's visiting.

09:29.612 --> 09:30.831
Ms. McCoy!

09:30.874 --> 09:32.484
-Oh!
-[Josie laughs]

09:32.528 --> 09:34.530
As fabulous as ever.

09:34.574 --> 09:36.401
Ah, thanks, Mr. Weatherbee.

09:36.445 --> 09:39.622
Now, what brings
a star like you
back to our humble halls?

09:39.666 --> 09:42.538
Yeah, inquiring minds
want to know.

09:42.582 --> 09:45.062
Actually, I have
a favor to ask.

09:45.106 --> 09:47.064
I'm here to do
some song writing,
and I was wondering

09:47.108 --> 09:49.719
if I could use
the music room to record.

09:49.763 --> 09:51.939
Of course I'd pay top dollar.

09:51.982 --> 09:54.071
Just name your price.

09:54.115 --> 09:57.901
Can your payment be teaching
a music class
at Riverdale High?

09:57.945 --> 10:01.252
It hasn't exactly been
the easiest year
for our students.

10:01.296 --> 10:03.603
For you guys,
I'll happily do it.

10:03.646 --> 10:05.648
That's fantastic news.

10:05.692 --> 10:07.737
They'll be so excited.
[laughs]

10:07.781 --> 10:09.217
[phone ringing]

10:11.393 --> 10:12.437
Smithers, what's going on?

10:12.481 --> 10:14.309
[suspenseful music playing]

10:15.136 --> 10:17.181
Uh, send her in.

10:22.709 --> 10:24.275
Alexandra Cabot.

10:24.319 --> 10:25.929
What are you doing
in Riverdale?

10:25.973 --> 10:28.497
[sighs] Veronica Lodge.

10:28.540 --> 10:30.673
Well, I could ask
the same thing,

10:30.717 --> 10:36.766
but I am here about
some investments that I made,
with your squirrelly husband.

10:36.810 --> 10:39.203
I've been calling Chad,
but he's MIA.

10:39.247 --> 10:42.946
So, I made a day trip
to pull my money out.

10:42.990 --> 10:46.471
I'm feeling fiscally antsy,
you see.

10:46.515 --> 10:48.386
Of course.

10:48.430 --> 10:50.911
And I could absolutely

10:50.954 --> 10:53.609
give you
the money back
right now...

10:53.653 --> 10:56.046
-Or...
-Or...

10:56.090 --> 11:01.269
Well, I just stumbled across
this new investment opportunity

11:01.312 --> 11:05.360
that I'm extremely,
extremely excited about.

11:05.403 --> 11:08.015
Out of curiosity.

11:08.058 --> 11:10.234
How do you feel
about diners?

11:10.278 --> 11:11.845
Hmm...

11:11.888 --> 11:13.324
Tell me more.

11:13.368 --> 11:17.677
♪ Can't you see
The clouds gathering ♪

11:17.720 --> 11:23.291
♪ There's a brand new feeling
In the air ♪

11:23.334 --> 11:27.687
♪ Better run to the ark
Before the rain starts ♪

11:27.730 --> 11:29.166
No way.

11:29.210 --> 11:31.168
♪ You better come
On in this house ♪

11:31.212 --> 11:33.388
-♪ It's gonna rain
-♪ It's gonna rain

11:33.431 --> 11:35.738
♪ Rain down fire

11:35.782 --> 11:38.001
♪ It's gonna rain

11:38.045 --> 11:40.656
♪ You better come
On in this house ♪

11:40.700 --> 11:43.528
-♪ It's gonna rain
-♪ It's gonna rain

11:43.572 --> 11:46.009
♪ Rain down fire

11:46.053 --> 11:48.490
♪ It's gonna rain

11:48.533 --> 11:49.534
[music stops]

11:49.578 --> 11:52.015
[all cheering]

11:53.234 --> 11:55.279
Really good.

11:56.803 --> 11:59.501
[sighs]
Oh, my gosh.
[chuckles]

11:59.544 --> 12:01.111
Archie Andrews!

12:01.155 --> 12:02.243
Josie.

12:02.286 --> 12:04.767
-I knew it was you.
-[Josie chuckles]

12:04.811 --> 12:09.380
Oh, hi.
[chuckles]

12:09.424 --> 12:13.602
And now I'm back in Riverdale
to work on this new album.

12:13.645 --> 12:15.909
Hey, you should come
to the Whyte Wyrm tonight.

12:15.952 --> 12:17.737
Formerly, the speakeasy.

12:17.780 --> 12:19.260
Everyone would love to see you.

12:19.303 --> 12:22.045
I actually have
some song writing
I need to do.

12:22.089 --> 12:23.612
Oh, come on.
Just for a drink or two.

12:23.655 --> 12:25.135
It's' been, what,
seven years?

12:25.179 --> 12:27.268
Yeah, something like that.

12:28.660 --> 12:30.837
Okay.

12:30.880 --> 12:32.229
But can I meet you there?

12:32.273 --> 12:34.057
I have some phone calls
I need to make.

12:34.101 --> 12:36.581
[Melody]
Give you two guesses
who Josie called.

12:36.625 --> 12:38.540
[cell phone ringing]

12:41.586 --> 12:45.112
I freaked
and sent her to voicemail.

12:45.155 --> 12:49.333
At which point,
a phone in the living room
started to ring.

12:51.074 --> 12:53.294
Hey, Josie, what's up?

12:55.644 --> 12:59.082
No, we even made this, uh,
this sexy fireman's calendar

12:59.126 --> 13:00.649
to raise money
for the fire station.

13:00.692 --> 13:02.825
But anyway,
enough about me.

13:02.869 --> 13:04.871
How about you, Josie?

13:04.914 --> 13:07.743
Well, it's been a whirlwind.

13:07.787 --> 13:09.092
Oh, don't worry, Josie.

13:09.136 --> 13:11.616
I've kept them all apprised
from your special

13:11.660 --> 13:14.924
on Entertainment Tomorrow
to your Vanity Flaircover.

13:14.968 --> 13:16.926
It's so great
that you're here, Josie.

13:16.970 --> 13:18.885
You could help us
save Riverdale.

13:18.928 --> 13:22.062
We've been needing a face,
a celebrity to help
get people excited.

13:22.105 --> 13:24.151
Guys, give her a minute.
She just got here.

13:24.194 --> 13:27.197
Oh, we should do
a benefit concert.

13:27.241 --> 13:29.634
That would be so much fun.
Just like old times.

13:29.678 --> 13:31.288
Old times?
[scoffs]

13:31.332 --> 13:33.813
I don't mean
to offend you, Veronica,

13:33.856 --> 13:36.598
but I didn't have
much of a say
in our old times.

13:36.641 --> 13:39.296
And at this point,
we're more acquaintances
than friends.

13:39.340 --> 13:40.384
Yikes!

13:40.428 --> 13:42.299
Oh, Jughead.
The last time I saw you,

13:42.343 --> 13:45.607
you were robbing
Pop Tate's at gunpoint
in a Serpents' mask.

13:45.650 --> 13:47.696
[man] Everybody on the ground
right now!

13:47.739 --> 13:49.002
[man 2] Get down!

13:49.611 --> 13:50.830
Uh...

13:50.873 --> 13:52.483
Josie, that was
so many years ago.

13:52.527 --> 13:55.095
Uh-uh, Betty,
you and I have spoken
all of what?

13:55.138 --> 13:56.487
One time in high school?

13:56.531 --> 13:58.794
If I could just jump in
for a moment.

13:58.838 --> 14:01.884
None of you townies
deserve to be in the presence
of such musical greatness.

14:01.928 --> 14:04.495
Cheryl, you once sent me
a pig's heart.

14:04.539 --> 14:07.194
[gasps heavily]

14:07.237 --> 14:09.022
Which is something
that still haunts me.

14:09.065 --> 14:11.894
So jump down
off that soapbox, shall we?

14:14.027 --> 14:16.856
I came to Riverdale
to make an album,

14:16.899 --> 14:18.031
not to cause trouble.

14:18.074 --> 14:20.424
So if you'll kindly
excuse me.

14:30.608 --> 14:32.175
Josie McCoy.

14:33.394 --> 14:34.395
Sweet Pea?

14:34.438 --> 14:36.092
What are you doing
at Pop's?

14:37.572 --> 14:38.616
Leaving.

14:38.660 --> 14:40.183
Well, do you want a ride?

14:42.664 --> 14:43.883
Wherever you're going.

14:51.064 --> 14:54.241
♪ I don't wanna go

14:56.765 --> 14:58.941
♪ I don't wanna go

15:00.247 --> 15:02.292
[music fades, stops]

15:11.084 --> 15:13.390
Sneaking out
of your own hotel room?

15:13.434 --> 15:17.525
Sweat Pea, last night
was exactly what I needed.

15:19.005 --> 15:21.964
But I've got things to do
and people to meet.

15:22.008 --> 15:25.098
Of course,
you're a busy star.

15:28.666 --> 15:30.364
[both chuckle]

15:33.106 --> 15:34.672
[blows kiss]

15:35.760 --> 15:37.240
Bye, stud.

15:41.418 --> 15:44.595
[Josie] Val, Mel,
thank you for meeting me here.

15:44.639 --> 15:47.424
How have you both been doing?
What are you doing?

15:47.468 --> 15:49.557
I've been doing a lot of art

15:49.600 --> 15:52.038
and getting into
political activism.

15:52.081 --> 15:53.474
Val is going
to save the world.

15:53.517 --> 15:55.171
One peaceful protest
at a time.

15:55.215 --> 15:56.999
That's really amazing, Val.

15:57.043 --> 15:58.696
How about you, Melody?

15:59.828 --> 16:02.004
[chuckles]
I stay busy.

16:02.048 --> 16:03.179
I'm a YA novelist.

16:03.223 --> 16:04.702
I just had
my first book published.

16:04.746 --> 16:06.835
I thought I heard
something about that.

16:06.878 --> 16:09.881
Tyler Perry's producing
a movie of it, right?
It's, um, starring--

16:09.925 --> 16:12.058
What about you, Josie?

16:12.101 --> 16:14.016
What brings you
to Riverdale?

16:14.582 --> 16:15.452
[chuckles]

16:15.496 --> 16:19.804
I needed a break from my tour,

16:19.848 --> 16:21.981
thought I'd finally write
about my hometown.

16:22.024 --> 16:27.682
And since you guys
were a big part
of my experience here,

16:27.725 --> 16:31.816
I'd love to have you join me
on one of the tracks.

16:31.860 --> 16:34.732
I mean, I don't know
if either of you
do any performing still.

16:34.776 --> 16:36.952
[crowd cheering]

16:36.996 --> 16:40.477
♪ Common love isn't for us

16:40.521 --> 16:43.132
