[crowd cheering]

20:00.329 --> 20:03.941
Yeah, we still do
a little bit of performing
on the side.

20:03.985 --> 20:06.335
-Music was my first love, so.
-[Valerie] Mine, too.

20:06.379 --> 20:10.209
Which is why it was so hard
when you just disappeared
on us, Josie.

20:10.252 --> 20:11.732
I know, I know I did,

20:11.775 --> 20:14.735
but when I got the opportunity
to tour with my dad--

20:14.778 --> 20:17.346
We're not talking
about that, Josie.

20:17.390 --> 20:19.566
We're talking about
before you left town.

20:19.609 --> 20:23.134
When you stopped calling us,
we stopped hanging out.
Stop playing gigs.

20:23.178 --> 20:24.875
We thought we'd done
something wrong.

20:24.919 --> 20:29.880
And the irony of that
is that your dad
was like us, a side man.

20:29.924 --> 20:32.448
You'd think that you,
of all people,
would have respected

20:32.492 --> 20:34.450
your side women
a little bit more.

20:36.104 --> 20:38.106
I'm sorry.

20:38.149 --> 20:41.414
Truly, I am.
I know the value
of what you both did

20:41.457 --> 20:44.025
and what you brought
to the table.

20:44.068 --> 20:47.028
And I understand
if you don't want
to record this song,

20:47.071 --> 20:48.551
but it's an open offer.

20:49.335 --> 20:51.293
We'll think about it.

20:51.337 --> 20:56.037
But either way,
it was good catching up
with you, Josie.

20:56.080 --> 20:58.300
I like to think of myself
as a connector.

20:58.344 --> 21:01.782
My friend, Tabitha Tate,
wants to franchise
her family's diner.

21:01.825 --> 21:03.610
And my other friend,
Alexandra Cabot,

21:03.653 --> 21:05.742
is always looking
for a smart investment.

21:05.786 --> 21:09.572
Tabitha,
why don't you tell Xandra
what you told me last night?

21:09.616 --> 21:12.401
I believe that America
is ready for a new start.

21:12.445 --> 21:15.926
And I believe the face
of that new start should be
Pop's Chock'lit Shoppe,

21:15.970 --> 21:18.581
small town feel,
even in big cities.

21:18.625 --> 21:20.409
Oh, and please feel free
to look through our packet,

21:20.453 --> 21:22.281
it details
our expansion strategy.

21:22.324 --> 21:23.543
No need.

21:23.586 --> 21:25.153
I've already made
my decision.

21:25.196 --> 21:29.592
I love diners
and I'm feeling your
homespun vision.

21:29.636 --> 21:31.942
But may I suggest
a tweak or two?

21:32.639 --> 21:34.423
What kind of tweaks?

21:34.467 --> 21:35.946
Well, you may not know
this about me,

21:35.990 --> 21:38.775
but I am a performer
as well as a businesswoman.

21:38.819 --> 21:43.563
And I've always romanticized
singing diners.

21:43.606 --> 21:46.914
Yeah, we have a proud tradition
of singing here at Pop's.

21:47.349 --> 21:48.829
Mmm.

21:48.872 --> 21:51.310
Singing is something
we can definitely talk about.

21:51.353 --> 21:54.225
Oh, yeah, talking isn't exactly
what I had in mind.

21:54.269 --> 21:56.097
[upbeat music playing]

21:56.140 --> 21:59.100
♪ Little Shop
Little Shop o' Horrors ♪

21:59.143 --> 22:02.059
